content: No one really knows how the species known as the Molluscoids evolved to become the hyper muscular sentient species they are now. content: None of the known biological civilisations in the Pixel Invaderz galaxy want to take blame, for what originally was supposed to be a secure diplomatic force, meant to protect destabilized systems from political collapse. Instead, the race known as the Roboids came to be a prominent figure in galactic politics becoming a threat to all biological life and especially their creators. For now, the rouge AI-Empire can be contained to their territory through a collected effort of the strongest civilisations in the galaxy.

The Monovrachs are incapable of reproduction, but consider their pre-molten body their parent.
title: Pixelinvader #3826

content: The Sartapeds are a very invasive species, having conquered a big part of their neighboring systems almost by accident. Through the centuries, their race has achieved enormous growth in population, intelligence and military technology. This is mostly due to them feasting on the minds of their enemies.
title: Pixelinvader #3832

content: Living underground for the past 3 million years the Antoids developed the ability to live out on the surface of their home planet in only the past 10.000 years, which sparked an exponential growth that brought their civilisations to space, thus making them part of the galactic community.
title: Pixelinvader #3965

content: The Manitoris share parts of their domain with the Fungoids and act as their negotiators while still ruling over their own empire. They only have one eye that leaves them almost blind, as it omits spores, which causes them to have very blurry vision. In response, they evolved to grow mycelium at an incredible rate to communicate and navigate around their colonies.
title: Pixelinvader #4017

content: The creatures of darkness. The Gotilos live in the darkest places of the galaxy. They are the only known species that has ever lived on planets revolving around a black hole. Their only mission: Extinguishing every sun in the known universe.
title: Pixelinvader #4022

content: The Zapitan have been at war for habitable planets with the Kormoids for centuries now. Other than their ongoing battle for the coldest planets in the galaxy, the Zapitan seem to be benevolent creatures, helping stranded warm-blooded species survive in the harsh climate of their colonies.
title: Pixelinvader #4200

content: No one really knows how the species known as the Molluscoids evolved to become the hyper muscular sentient species they are now. An even bigger mystery is their home planet, as it is covered in an opaque atmosphere and no one besides themselves ever stepped foot on it. Molluscoids are generally hostile towards other species and have no diplomatic ties with other civilisations.
title: Pixelinvader #4271

content: Where they came from is still unclear, but the Yperan seem to have existed for eons. They never interfered in the affairs of "lower life forms" for the longest time. But since the Age of Invasion began, even the Yperan have started their own empires and alliances as well.
title: Pixelinvader #4378

content: Where they came from is still unclear, but the Yperan seem to have existed for eons. They never interfered in the affairs of "lower life forms" for the longest time. But since the Age of Invasion began, even the Yperan have started their own empires and alliances as well.
title: Pixelinvader #4409

content: With their four arms, the Triamats were once a slave race, primarily used for construction. After many years of oppression, they started an uprising against their keepers and built their own empire. Sworn to never treat another species the way they were, their main goal became freeing other colonies from their shackles.
title: Pixelinvader #4530

content: A kind-hearted species that can be encountered on every planet with lush landscapes. Normally, the Dentrans use their connection to a planet's Flora to heal wounded Fauna, but they will lead war against other species if they cause harm to the Dentrans domain.
title: Pixelinvader #4626

content: Even though the Troculus possess the facial features of an Insectoid, they are mammals. This confusion had to be cleared up with the Vatiloids many times. With their fly-like eyes, the Troculus can detect even the slightest movement, which has helped them survive and gives them many advantages in battle.
title: Pixelinvader #4809

content: Nobody knows which species advanced to become this horrific mixture of machine and organic life. Even worse, Skoroids will not eliminate their enemies, but take them (still alive) to their nest. What happens threre is unclear, and further investigation on the Skoroids has been prohibited by the galaxy collectively as it is considered to be too dangerous. Even the Roboids retreat when encountering the Skoroids.
title: Pixelinvader #4922

content: Despite their scary appearance the Spidoids are known to be a very sociable and friendly species. It took them about 15 million years to evolve from small bug to big leggy boi. Growing a big brain turned out to take a little longer than you'd expect for other sentient species. Nevertheless, the race of the Spidoids built one of the most prominent space empires currently known to mankind.
title: Pixelinvader #4221

content: None of the known biological civilisations in the Pixel Invaderz galaxy want to take blame, for what originally was supposed to be a secure diplomatic force, meant to protect destabilized systems from political collapse. Instead, the race known as the Roboids came to be a prominent figure in galactic politics becoming a threat to all biological life and especially their creators. For now, the rouge AI-Empire can be contained to their territory through a collected effort of the strongest civilisations in the galaxy.
